comparison of american and british engli.data-term: comparison of american and british english

examples.en: He claimed that he'd been cheated.
She realized that she had been cheated.
The clever salesman cheated the old lady into giving him all her money.
She claimed that I cheated at chess.
He whined to us that he had been cheated.
It is possible that Fred cheated at the exam.
He contended that he had been cheated.
These people have been hocused and cheated by the Government.
They cheated him out of a fair deal.
Jim said that his brother had cheated at cards.
Illegal workers are often cheated by employers.
He had cheated in the test by using a calculator.
They narrowly cheated death in a 65mph van crash.
She didn't like his insinuation that she had cheated.
The Italian ace cheated death in a spectacular 100 mph crash.
He spoke gloatingly about people he had cheated out of their money.
I will not condescend to answer the sore loser's charge that I cheated in order to win the race.
When you feel you've been cheated, it always leaves a nasty taste in the mouth (=makes you feel upset or angry afterwards).
